        ],
        "documentHtml": "<section style=\"margin:0 0 20px 0;\"><div style=\"display:flex;flex-direction:column;box-sizing:border-box;padding:20px;border-radius:20px;background:linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(255,252,245,0.99), rgba(255,248,235,0.96));border:1px solid rgba(146,64,14,0.16);box-shadow:0 12px 28px rgba(180,83,9,0.10);gap:14px;\"><div style=\"display:flex;align-items:flex-start;justify-content:space-between;gap:12px;\"><div style=\"display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:6px;min-width:0;\"><div style=\"font:700 11px/1.2 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;letter-spacing:0.18em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#b45309;\">Title</div><div style=\"font:700 28px/1.12 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;color:#1f2937;word-break:break-word;\">GitHub How-To</div></div><div style=\"display:flex;flex-direction:column;align-items:flex-end;gap:6px;flex-shrink:0;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 8px;border-radius:999px;background:rgba(180,83,9,0.1);color:#92400e;font-size:11px;font-weight:700;letter-spacing:0.04em;\">headline</span><span style=\"font:600 10px/1.2 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;letter-spacing:0.12em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#9a3412;opacity:0.72;\">active</span></div></div><div style=\"height:1px;background:linear-gradient(90deg, rgba(245,158,11,0.45), rgba(245,158,11,0));\"></div><div style=\"font:500 15px/1.65 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;color:#4b5563;\">Practical guide for connecting Twilite to GitHub: start in browser chrome, read the status surfaces, choose the right installation, and save intentionally when the task calls for a write.</div></div></section><section style=\"margin:0 0 20px 0;\"><div style=\"display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:14px;padding:20px;border-radius:20px;background:linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(255,255,255,0.99), rgba(248,250,252,0.96));border:1px solid rgba(15,23,42,0.12);box-shadow:0 12px 28px rgba(15,23,42,0.08);\"><div style=\"display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:space-between;gap:12px;\"><div id=\"status-strip\" style=\"font:700 24px/1.15 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;color:#111827;\">Read the status strip first</div><div style=\"display:flex;gap:6px;flex-wrap:wrap;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 8px;border-radius:999px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.14);color:#1d4ed8;font-size:11px;font-weight:600;\">Section</span></div></div><div style=\"height:4px;border-radius:999px;background:linear-gradient(90deg, #2563eb, #60a5fa);opacity:0.95;\"></div><div style=\"font:500 15px/1.7 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;color:#1f2937;\">The status surfaces are the authoritative summary layer. `Document` tells you what graph is open, `Save target` tells you where the next write is pointed, and `Access` tells you which installation context Twilite is using. If `Document` and `Save target` disagree, resolve that before writing.</div></div></section><section style=\"margin:0 0 20px 0;\"><div style=\"display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:14px;padding:20px;border-radius:20px;background:linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(255,255,255,0.99), rgba(248,250,252,0.96));border:1px solid rgba(15,23,42,0.12);box-shadow:0 12px 28px rgba(15,23,42,0.08);\"><div style=\"display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:space-between;gap:12px;\"><div id=\"save-flow\" style=\"font:700 24px/1.15 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;color:#111827;\">Save a graph to GitHub</div><div style=\"display:flex;gap:6px;flex-wrap:wrap;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 8px;border-radius:999px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.14);color:#1d4ed8;font-size:11px;font-weight:600;\">Section</span></div></div><div style=\"height:4px;border-radius:999px;background:linear-gradient(90deg, #2563eb, #60a5fa);opacity:0.95;\"></div><div style=\"font:500 15px/1.7 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;color:#1f2937;\">Open `Save to GitHub`, choose the installation that can actually see the destination repo, then choose repository, branch, and path. Read the capability pill next to the save button. `Writable` means high confidence for a direct write, `Accessible` means GitHub can reach the destination but Twilite cannot fully predict the final outcome, and `Blocked` means the selected installation cannot access that repo directly.</div></div></section><section style=\"margin:0 0 20px 0;\"><div style=\"display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:14px;padding:20px;border-radius:20px;background:linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(255,255,255,0.99), rgba(248,250,252,0.96));border:1px solid rgba(15,23,42,0.12);box-shadow:0 12px 28px rgba(15,23,42,0.08);\"><div style=\"display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:space-between;gap:12px;\"><div id=\"missing-repos\" style=\"font:700 24px/1.15 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;color:#111827;\">If a repo is missing</div><div style=\"display:flex;gap:6px;flex-wrap:wrap;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 8px;border-radius:999px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.14);color:#1d4ed8;font-size:11px;font-weight:600;\">Section</span></div></div><div style=\"height:4px;border-radius:999px;background:linear-gradient(90deg, #2563eb, #60a5fa);opacity:0.95;\"></div><div style=\"font:500 15px/1.7 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;color:#1f2937;\">Missing repos are usually an installation-scope issue on GitHub, not a local-folder issue. Local folders do not make a repo visible to Twilite, and workspace mappings are defaults rather than proof of GitHub authority. The repo picker only shows repos returned by the selected GitHub App installation.</div></div></section><section style=\"margin:0 0 20px 0;\"><div style=\"display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:14px;padding:20px;border-radius:20px;background:linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(255,255,255,0.99), rgba(248,250,252,0.96));border:1px solid rgba(15,23,42,0.12);box-shadow:0 12px 28px rgba(15,23,42,0.08);\"><div style=\"display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:space-between;gap:12px;\"><div id=\"mental-model\" style=\"font:700 24px/1.15 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;color:#111827;\">Keep the model separate</div><div style=\"display:flex;gap:6px;flex-wrap:wrap;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 8px;border-radius:999px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.14);color:#1d4ed8;font-size:11px;font-weight:600;\">Section</span></div></div><div style=\"height:4px;border-radius:999px;background:linear-gradient(90deg, #2563eb, #60a5fa);opacity:0.95;\"></div><div style=\"font:500 15px/1.7 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;color:#1f2937;\">Twilite&#39;s current GitHub integration works best when five ideas stay separate: document identity, browse path, save target, installation access, and workspace defaults. The product is safer when those are exposed explicitly instead of being hidden behind one generic GitHub state.</div></div></section><section style=\"margin:0 0 20px 0;\"><div style=\"display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:14px;padding:20px;border-radius:20px;background:linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(255,255,255,0.99), rgba(248,250,252,0.96));border:1px solid rgba(15,23,42,0.12);box-shadow:0 12px 28px rgba(15,23,42,0.08);\"><div style=\"display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:space-between;gap:12px;\"><div style=\"font:700 24px/1.15 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;color:#111827;\">Summary</div><div style=\"display:flex;gap:6px;flex-wrap:wrap;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 8px;border-radius:999px;background:rgba(219,39,119,0.14);color:#9d174d;font-size:11px;font-weight:600;\">Summary</span></div></div><div style=\"height:4px;border-radius:999px;background:linear-gradient(90deg, #db2777, #f472b6);opacity:0.95;\"></div><div style=\"font:500 15px/1.7 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;color:#1f2937;\">The GitHub how-to is the practical operating surface: start in browser chrome, read the status surfaces, choose the installation that can actually see the destination repo, save intentionally, and interpret `Writable`, `Accessible`, and `Blocked` as save-time signals rather than as workspace-mapping state.</div><div style=\"font:600 12px/1.4 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;color:#64748b;\">Scope: GitHub how-to</div></div></section>",
